2%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f988524af076d3cf91932b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22697%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Long%20March-5B%20Y3%20rocket%20leaves%20the%20Wenchang%20Spacecraft%20Launch%20Site%20in%20southern%20China%20on%20July%2024%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EChina%20News%20Service%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EChina%20may%20be%20planning%20to%20take%20out%20US%20satellites%20from%20the%20moon%2C%20a%20US%20Space%20Force%20commander%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAnalysts%20are%20warning%20that%20China%20could%20be%20planning%20to%20use%20its%20power%20in%20space%20for%20military%20purposes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20others%20say%20that%20its%20ambitions%20may%20be%20difficult%20to%20realize.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20could%20be%20planning%20to%20attack%20US%20satellites%20from%20the%20Moon%2C%20a%20US%20Space%20Force%20commander%20said%2C%20amid%20growing%20US%20concerns%20about%20China's%20space%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defenseone.com%2Fthreats%2F2024%2F03%2Fchinas-moon-plans-worry-space-force%2F395043%2F%3Foref%3Ddefenseone_today_nl%26utm_source%3DSailthru%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3DDefense%2520One%2520Today%3A%2520March%252019%252C%25202024%26utm_term%3Dnewsletter_d1_today%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDefense%20One%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20comments%20from%20Brig.%20Gen.%20Anthony%20Mastalir%2C%20commander%20of%20US%20Space%20Forces%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20who%20discussed%20China's%20lunar%20exploration%20program%20at%20a%20conference%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20a%20military%20perspective%2C%20I%20am%20curious%20about%2C%20are%20there%20attack%20vectors%20that%20we%20haven't%20considered%20or%20that%20we%20need%20to%20consider%2C%20whether%20it's%20xGeo%20or%20cislunar%20or%20otherwise%3F%26quot%3B%20Mastalir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EXGeo%20is%20Space%20Force%20jargon%20for%20all%20of%20outer%2