p%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20Rosenberg%20wasn't%20deterred%20in%20his%20call.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20I'm%20Christopher%20Columbus%20in%201492%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20Isabella%20Ferdinand%2C%20trying%20to%20tell%20them%3A%20No%2C%20the%20world%20isn't%20flat%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DHkuJ2rEBoYg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20interview%20on%20Monday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20economist%20highlighted%20that%20real%20retail%20sales%20volumes%20are%20down%201.8%25%20and%20industrial%20production%20is%20down%205.6%25%20on%20an%20annual%20basis%20in%20the%20first%20quarter.%20The%20historical%20patterns%20show%20that%20such%20simultaneous%20contractions%20in%20real%20retail%20sales%20and%20production%20typically%20herald%20the%20arrival%20of%20an%20economic%20downturn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%5BH%5Distorically%2C%20when%20that's%20happening%2C%20unless%20it's%20an%20aberration%2C%20you%20have%20a%20four%20times%20greater%20chance%20of%20being%20in%20a%20recession%20than%20in%20an%20expansion.%20So%20it's%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20time%20before%20you%20know%20if%20the%20data%20flow%20continues%20the%20way%20it%20has%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20months.%20I%20think%20the%20recession%20narrative%20is%20going%20to%20come%20back%2C%20you%20know%2C%20in%20a%2C%20in%20a%20fuller%20view%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenberg%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20pointed%20to%20the%20job%20sector%2C%20noting%20that%20even%20though%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20still%20appears%20low%2C%20there's%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20dichotomy%26quot%3B%20in%20job%20claims%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20spot%20claim%20numbers%20have%20remained%20exceptionally%20low%2C%20but%20it's%20telling%20you%20that%20companies%20are%20not%20firing%20people.%20However%2C%20look%20at%20the%20backlog%20of%20continuing%20claims.%20They've%20continued%20to%20rise.%20And%20what%20that's%20telling%20you%20is%20that%20it's%20getting%20tougher%20and%20tougher%20for%20the%20backlog%20of%20unemployed%20to%20find%20a%20new%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20cast%20doubt%20on%20the%20household%20survey's%20unemployment%20figure%2C%20arguing%20that%20all%20jobs%20created%20in%20the%20past%20year%20have%20been%20part-time%2C%20rendering%20many%20workers%20ineligible%20for%20unemployment%20insurance%20and%20potentially%20skewing%20the%20data%20downward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20can%20we%20be%20talking%20about%20a%20buoyant%20labor%20market%20when%20there%20has%20not%20been%20one%20net%20new%20full%20time%20job%20created%20in%20the%20United%20States%20over%20the%2012%20months%20of%20February%3F%20How%20do%20you%20square%20that%20circle%20to%20a%20narrative%20that%20we%20really%20have%20a%20robust%20labor%20market%20on%20our%20hands%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20questioned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-4-times-more-likely-than-expansion-david-rosenberg-economy-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710855428000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61f2e4ff2fd30f0018aee61b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-4-times-more-likely-than-expansion-david-rosenberg-economy-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20I'm%20Christopher%20Columbus%20in%201492%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20Isabella%20Ferdinand%2C%20trying%20to%20tell%20them%3A%20No%2C%20the%20world%20isn't%20flat%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenberg%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22yzhan%40insider.com%20(Yuheng%20Zhan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-4-times-more-likely-than-expansion-david-rosenberg-economy-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22t