20out%20that%20%26quot%3Bfossil%20fuel%20pollution%20is%20sending%20climate%20chaos%20off%20the%20charts%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20warning%20that%20%26quot%3Bchanges%20are%20speeding%20up%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WMO%20said%20the%20average%20near-surface%20temperature%20was%201.45%20degrees%20Celsius%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels%20last%20year%20--%20dangerously%20close%20to%20the%20critical%201.5-degree%20threshold%20that%20countries%20agreed%20to%20avoid%20passing%20in%20the%202015%20Paris%20climate%20accords.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNever%20have%20we%20been%20so%20close...%20to%20the%201.5C%20lower%20limit%20of%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%2C%26quot%3B%20WMO%20chief%20Andrea%20Celeste%20Saulo%20warned%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20'Red%20alert'%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20she%20said%2C%20should%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bred%20alert%20to%20the%20world%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20through%20the%20data%2C%20the%20organisation%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Brecords%20were%20once%20again%20broken%2C%20and%20in%20some%20cases%20smashed%26quot%3B%2C%20warning%20that%20the%20numbers%20%26quot%3Bgave%20ominous%20new%20significance%20to%20the%20phrase%20'off%20the%20charts'.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaulo%20stressed%20that%20climate%20change%20was%20about%20much%20more%20than%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20witnessed%20in%202023%2C%20especially%20with%20the%20unprecedented%20ocean%20warmth%2C%20glacier%20retreat%20and%20Antarctic%20sea%20ice%20loss%2C%20is%20cause%20for%20particular%20concern.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20especially%20worrying%20finding%20was%20that%20marine%20heatwaves%20gripped%20nearly%20a%20third%20of%20the%20global%20ocean%20on%20an%20average%20day%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20by%20the%20end%20of%202023%2C%20more%20than%2090%20percent%20of%20the%20ocean%20had%20experienced%20heatwave%20conditions%20at%20some%20point%20during%20the%20year%2C%20the%20WMO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20frequent%20and%20intense%20marine%20heatwaves%20will%20have%20%26quot%3Bprofound%20negative%20repercussions%20for%20marine%20ecosystems%20and%20coral%20reefs%26quot%3B%2C%20it%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20warned%20that%20key%20glaciers%20worldwide%20suffered%20the%20largest%20loss%20of%20ice%20ever%20since%20records%20began%20in%201950%2C%20%26quot%3Bdriven%20by%20extreme%20melt%20in%20both%20western%20North%20America%20and%20Europe%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Switzerland%2C%20where%20the%20WMO%20is%20headquartered%2C%20Alpine%20glaciers%20had%20for%20instance%20lost%2010%20percent%20of%20their%20remaining%20volume%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years%20alone%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Antarctic%20sea%20ice%20extent%20was%20also%20%26quot%3Bby%20far%20the%20lowest%20on%20record%26quot%3B%2C%20WMO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Rising%20sea%20levels%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20it%20pointed%20out%2C%20its%20maximum%20extent%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20southern%20winter%20was%20around%20one%20million%20square%20kilometres%20below%20the%20previous%20record%20year%20--%20equivalent%20to%20the%20size%20of%20France%20and%20Germany%20combined.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20continued%20ocean%20warming%20combined%20with%20the%20rapidly%20melting%20glaciers%20and%20ice%20sheets%20also%20drove%20the%20sea%20level%20last%20year%20to%20its%20highest%20point%20since%20satellite%20records%20began%20in%201993%2C%20WMO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20stressed%20that%20the%20global%20mean%20sea%20level%20rise%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20(2014-2023)%20was%20more%20than%20double%20the%20rate%20in%20the%20first%20decade%20of%20satellite%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20highlighted%20that%20the%20dramatic%20climate%20shifts%20are%20taking%20a%20heavy%20toll%20on%20people%20worldwide%2C%20fuelling%20extreme%20weather%20events%2C%20flooding%20and%20drought%2C%20which%20trigger%20displacement%20and%20drive%20up%20biodiversity%20loss%20and%20food%20insecurity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20climate%20crisis%20is%20THE%20defining%20challenge%20that%20humanity%20faces%20and%20is%20closely%20intertwined%20with%20the%20inequality%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20Saulo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20'Glimmer%20of%20hope'%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20people%20who%20are%20considered%20acutely%20food%20insecure%20around%20the%20world%20has%20more%20than%20doubled%2C%20from%20149%20million%20people%20prior%20to%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20to%20333%20million%20at%20the%20end%20of%202023%2C%20WMO%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UN's%20weather%20and%20climate%20agency%20did%20however%20highlight%20one%20%26quot%3Bglimmer%20of%20hope%26quot%3B%3A%20surging%20renewable%20energy%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20renewable%20energy%20generation%20capacity%20--%20mainly%20from%20solar%2C%20wind%20and%20hydropower%20--%20increased%20by%20nearly%2050%20percent%20from%202022%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGuterres%20also%20emphasised%20that%20there%20was%20an%20upside%20to%20the%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world%2C%20he%20insisted%2C%20still%20has%20a%20chance%20to%20keep%20the%20planet's%20long-term%20temperature%20rise%20below%20the%201.5C%20threshold%20and%20%26quot%3Bavoid%20the%20worst%20of%20climate%20chaos%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20how%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710854280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-06%2Fejdg1oc_global-warmingl_625x300_10_June_23.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fplanet-on-the-brink-un-as