0Instagram%20was%20so%20closely%20associated%20with%20the%20millennial%20aesthetic%20%E2%80%94%20avocado%20toast%2C%20emoji%20captions%2C%20the%20pressure%20to%20show%20off%20a%20sanitized%20and%20rosy%20view%20of%20one's%20life%20%E2%80%94%20that%20it%20seemed%20destined%20to%20go%20down%20(in%20coolness)%20with%20the%20millennial%20ship%20along%20with%20skinny%20jeans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F10%2F16%2Ftechnology%2Finstagram-teens.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Meta%20executives%20were%20freaking%20out%20about%20internal%20data%20showing%20that%20Instagram%20was%20losing%20favor%20with%20teens%2C%20and%20were%20pumping%20money%20into%20a%20marketing%20campaign%20to%20lure%20them%20back.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20The%20Atlantic%20declared%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Ftechnology%2Farchive%2F2022%2F11%2Finstagram-tiktok-twitter-social-media-competition%2F672305%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram%20Is%20Over.%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20It%20seemed%20like%20the%20nail%20was%20in%20the%20coffin.%20When%20The%20Atlantic%20says%20you're%20not%20cool%2C%20trust%20me%E2%80%A6%20you're%20not%20cool.%20They%20have%20fact-checkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20against%20all%20odds%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-playing-the-long-game-against-tiktok-and-winning-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram%20is%20staging%20its%20comeback%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESensor%20Tower%20shows%20that%20Instagram%20downloads%20were%20up%2020%25%20in%202023%20compared%20to%202022%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20TikTok's%204%25%20year-over-year%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstagram%20beat%20TikTok%20not%20only%20in%20growth%2C%20but%20sheer%20volume%20of%20app%20downloads%20in%202023%3A%20Instagram%20had%20767%20million%20while%20TikTok%20had%20733%20million.%20(TikTok%2C%20however%2C%20still%20beats%20Instagram%20in%20user%20engagement%20numbers).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat's%20driving%20Instagram's%20comeback%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcontent-na1.emarketer.com%2Finstagram-beat-tiktok-2023-downloads-fight-isn-t-over%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEMarketer%20suggests%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20few%20reasons%20for%20Instagram's%20success%20last%20year.%20One%20reason%20is%20Threads%2C%20the%20newly%20launched%20Twitter%20competitor%2C%20which%20requires%20an%20Instagram%20account%20and%20may%20have%20prompted%20some%20people%20who%20were%20curious%20about%20Threads%20to%20re-download%20Instagram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-threads-social-media-platform-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThreads%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20a%20surprising%20success.%20It%20had%20a%20record-breaking%20debut%20in%20July%20when%20over%20100%20million%20people%20downloaded%20it%20in%20the%20first%20week%20(thanks%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20Instagram%20prompted%20users%20to%20do%20so).%20Many%20of%20those%20curious%20early%20people%20quit%2C%20and%20for%20a%20while%20in%20late%20summer%2C%20the%20app%20seemed%20like%20tumbleweeds.%20But%20by%20December%202023%2C%20it%20was%20the%20most%20downloaded%20app%20in%20the%20App%20Store%20(it%20finally%20launched%20in%20Europe%20that%20month).%20Your%20mileage%20may%20vary%20in%20terms%20of%20how%20bullish%20you%20are%20on%20Threads%20continuing%20to%20be%20a%20fun%20or%20useful%20platform%2C%20but%20clearly%2C%20something's%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20thing%20for%20Instagram%20that%20seems%20to%20be%20working%20is%20Reels.%20When%20Reels%20launched%20in%202020%2C%20it%20wasn't%20an%20immediate%20success.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-reels-engagement-is-lagging-far-behind-rival-tiktok-report-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einternal%20report%20showed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Instagram%20was%20having%20trouble%20getting%20creators%20to%20actually%20post%2C%20despite%20having%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-reels-lure-tiktok-creators-cash-2020-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereportedly%20offered%20cash%20incentives%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20high-profile%20creators%2C%20and%20had%20low%20engagement%20from%20users%2C%20too.%20Even%20worse%2C%20lots%20of%20the%20videos%20were%20straight-up%20rips%20from%20Tiktok%2C%20watermark%20and%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20whether%20by%20hook%20or%20carrot%2C%20Reels%20content%20is%20suddenly%20more%20compelling.%20In%20fact%2C%20I've%20been%20enjoying%20Reels%20over%20TikTok%20lately%2C%20which%20is%20something%20I%20never%20would%20have%20predicted%20even%20six%20months%20ago.%20The%20key%3F%20I'm%20seeing%20more%20original%20videos%20and%20fewer%20reheated%20TikTok%20leftovers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Reels%20has%20improved%2C%20Instagram's%20traditional%20feed%20has%20changed.%20The%20feed%20now%20features%20fewer%20posts%20from%20friends%20and%20offers%20more%20suggested%20posts%20and%20Reels.%20Some%20creators%20aren't%20happy%20with%20the%20changes%20%E2%80%94%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkylie-jenner-kim-kardashian-instagram-stop-trying-to-be-tiktok-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKim%20Kardashian%20and%20Kylie%20Jenner%20complained%20publicly%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20new%20emphasis%20on%20Reels%20content.%20Head%20of%20Instagram%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagrams-adam-mosseri-spills-on-podcast-threads-creator-monetization-dms-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAdam%20Mosseri%20has%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bgrid%20photos%26quot%3B%20have%20been%20deemphasized%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20users%20are%20most%20active%20in%20Stories%2C%20DMs%2C%20and%20Reels.%20This%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20chicken-and-egg%20situation%3A%20users%20are%20more%20into%20Stories%20and%20Reels%20because%20their%20friends%20don't%20post%20to%20News%20Feed%2C%20but%20also%20people%20don't%20post%20to%20News%20Feed%20because%20they%20know%20no%20one%20sees%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20slightly%20frustrating%20part%20of%20Instagram's%20recent%20success%3A%20it%20suggests%20that%20Instagram%20has%20dominated%20not%20because%20of%20innovation%20or%20creative%20new%20features%2C%20but%20because%20of%20the%20sheer%20might%20of%20its%20massive%20user%20base.%20What%20I%20find%20exciting%20about%20technology%20and%20new%20apps%20is%20that%20they%20can%20give%20us%20a%20fun%20new%20way%20to%20communicate%20and%20play.%20New%20innovative%20apps%20like%20BeReal%20and%20Clubhouse%20were%20fun%2C%20even%20if%20they%20ultimately%20lost%20steam.%20Instagram%20Stories%20is%20a%20copy%20of%20Snapchat%2C%20and%20Reels%20is%20a%20copy%20of%20TikTok.%20Instagram%20hasn't%20had%20a%20truly%20innovative%20new%20feature%20since%20the%20Valencia%20filter.%20(Yes%2C%20Instagram%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-fights-back-against-emerging-apps-like-bereal-lapse-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etested%20a%20BeReal%20clone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-now-copies-bereal-instagram-daily-photo-video-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eso%20did%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E).%20But%20I%20digress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETikTok%20is%20getting%20old%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20TikTok%2C%20once%20the%20main%20existential%20crisis%20for%20Instagram%20(well%2C%20probably%20still%20is)%2C%20is%20faltering.%20According%20to%20data%20cited%20in%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Ftech%2Fpersonal-tech%2Fquitting-tiktok-less-swiping-more-sleeping-1e166a39%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20TikTok's%20monthly%20active%20users%20between%20ages%2018-24%20actually%20went%20down%209%25%20from%202022%20to%202023.%20Ouch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwentysomethings%20are%20spending%20less%20time%20on%20the%20app%20because%2C%20well%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-growth-collapsed-life-getting-in-way-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elife%20gets%20in%20the%20way%3C%2Fa%3E.%20TikTok%20surged%20during%20the%20pandemic%20when%20many%20people%20were%20stuck%20at%20home%20and%20looking%20for%20entertainment%20and%20connection.%20In%20my%20reporting%2C%20the%20most%20common%20thing%20I%20hear%20from%20any%20creator%20about%20when%20or%20why%20they%20started%20posting%20on%20TikTok%20is%20that%20they%20were%20bored%20during%20lockdown.%20The%20world%20is%20different%20now%2C%20and%20some%20of%20those%20high%20school%20kids%20whose%20screen%20time%20went%20wild%20in%202020%20are%20spending%20their%20days%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20is%20also%20greying%20%E2%80%94%20a%20recent%20Pew%20survey%20found%20the%20surprising%20news%20that%20the%20app%20once%20known%20for%20being%20mainly%20for%20teens%20now%20is%20popular%20with%20people%20over%20(gasp)%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%20Broderick%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.garbageday.email%2Fp%2Ftiktok-millennials-turns%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGarbage%20Day%20newsletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20summed%20up%20this%20depressing%20info%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EPew%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20there%20are%20actually%20less%20young%20people%20on%20TikTok%20right%20now%20than%20there%20were%20on%20Instagram%20in%202014.%20Almost%2040%25%20of%20TikTok%20users%20are%20in%20their%2030s%20and%2040s.%20In%202014%2C%20that%20same%20age%20group%20(which%20we%20are%20trying%20not%20to%20refer%20to%20as%20middle-aged)%20accounted%20for%20only%20about%2020%25%20of%20Instagram%20users.%20Even%20crazier%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EPew%3C%2Fem%3E's%20survey%2C%20people%20aged%2035-49%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20actually%20upload%20videos%20than%20people%20aged%2018-34.%20And%2C%20perhaps%20most%20damning%20of%20all%2C%20TikTok's%2030-49%20demographic%20is%20actually%20growing%20faster%20than%20the%2018-34%20cohort.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EYou'd%20think%20that%20the%20broader%20age%20range%20on%20TikTok%20would%20mean%20even%20worse%20news%20for%20Instagram.%20But%20somehow%2C%20it%20isn't.%20Maybe%20it's%20that%20TikTok%20is%20getting%20less%20cool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20gripe%20I've%20heard%20from%20lots%20of%20people%2C%20and%20sympathize%20with%20enormously%2C%20is%20that%20TikTok's%20emphasis%20on%20shopping%20has%20made%20the%20app%20less%20fun.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-trying-turn-shopping-creators-into-stars-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%20Shop%3C%2Fa%3E%20launched%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202023%2C%20and%20almost%20instantly%20it%20made%20the%20app%20feel%20noticeably%20more%20full%20of%20ads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20our%20purposes%20here%2C%20let's%20set%20aside%20the%20issue%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-bill-explained-politics-tech-platform-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%20ban%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20bill%20has%20passed%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%20that%20would%20force%20ByteDance%20to%20sell%20TikTok%20to%20a%20US%20buyer%20or%20effectively%20ban%20it.%20It's%20unclear%20what%20will%20happen%20if%20and%20when%20this%20bill%20reaches%20the%20Senate.%20Obviously%2C%20eliminating%20its%20competition%20would%20be%20good%20for%20Instagram%2C%20but%20overall%2C%20I'm%20not%20so%20sure%20that%20Congress%20being%20willing%20to%20go%20full%20scorched%20earth%20on%20the%20regulation%20of%20social%20media%20apps%20would%20be%20great%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20is%20currently%20engaged%20in%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20struggle%20with%20legislation%20and%20regulation%20around%20the%20potential%20of%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-sue-meta-allege-facebook-instagram-harm-youth-mental-health-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eharms%20to%20young%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20around%20mental%20health.%20There's%20new%20momentum%20around%20the%20idea%20of%20restricting%20social%20media%20to%20just%20older%20teens%2C%20and%20even%20limiting%20teens'%20access%20to%20phones%20at%20all.%20Schools%20are%20getting%20on%20board%2C%20and%20instituting%20phone-free%20policies%20in%20high%20schools.%20Yondr%2C%20a%20company%20that%20makes%20device-locking%20pouches%20initially%20made%20for%20comedy%20clubs%20and%20concerts%2C%20is%20now%20selling%20its%20products%20to%20high%20schools%2C%20and%20quite%20successfully%20%E2%80%94%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bostonglobe.com%2F2024%2F03%2F06%2Fmetro%2Fnew-cellphone-policy-for-brockton-high-school%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoston%20Globe%2C%20at%20least%2050%20schools%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Massachusetts%20use%20Yondr%20bags.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20possible%20that%20now%20that%20Instagram%20has%20managed%20to%20claw%20its%20way%20back%20past%20TikTok%2C%20it%20will%20have%20to%20face%20the%20final%20boss%3A%20competition%20against%20real%2C%20screen-free%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-instagram-stories-reels-made-comeback-beat-tiktok-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710851252000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f8afa64af076d3cf918052%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-instagram-stories-reels-made-comeback-beat-tiktok-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Instagram%20has%20fended%20off%20the%20existential%20threat%20of%20TikTok%2C%20and