%20can%20sometimes%20be%20necessary%20for%20your%20mental%20health.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20general%2C%20estrangement%20should%20be%20used%20as%20a%20tool%20for%20healing%20a%20relationship%2C%20a%20psychologist%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMonitor%20your%20resilience%20to%20hurtful%20remarks%20in%20other%20situations%20before%20reconnecting%20with%20a%20parent%2C%C2%A0he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDistancing%20yourself%20from%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-maintain-good-healthy-relationship-with-parents-adult-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edifficult%20parent%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20painful%2C%20but%20necessary.%20Some%20parents%20are%20so%20destructive%2C%20critical%2C%20and%20abusive%20that%20an%20adult%20child%20has%20no%20option%20but%20to%20choose%20between%20their%20own%20mental%20health%20and%20the%20parent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20general%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdivorce-healed-family-estrangement-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestrangements%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20be%20thought%20of%20as%20something%20you%20can%20resurface%20from%20after%20a%20period%20of%20time%20to%20see%20if%20anything%20has%20changed%2C%20Dr.%20Joshua%20Coleman%2C%20a%20psychologist%20and%20parental%20estrangement%20expert%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColeman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-to-cut-off-ties-go-no-contact-family-estrangement-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefines%20estrangement%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20going%20no%20or%20very%20little%20contact%20in%20a%20relationship%2C%20and%20said%20that%20more%20people%20are%20estranged%20from%20family%20members%20than%20ever.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOne%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1111%2Fjomf.12898%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20looked%20at%20interviews%20from%20thousands%20of%20American%20adult%20children%20found%20that%2026%25%20were%20or%20had%20been%20estranged%20from%20their%20father%20at%20some%20point%2C%20while%206%25%20were%20or%20previously%20had%20been%20cut%20off%20from%20their%20mother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColeman%20said%20that%20abuse%20is%20probably%20the%20most%20common%20reason%20cited%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-break-the-cycle-of-abuse-families-therapist-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecutting%20off%20a%20parent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20believes%20that%20generational%20differences%20play%20a%20big%20role.%20Over%20the%20past%20three%20decades%2C%20there's%20been%20an%20enormous%20expansion%20of%20what%20we%20consider%20to%20be%20harmful%2C%20abusive%2C%20neglectful%2C%20traumatizing%20behavior%2C%20he%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYounger%20generations%2C%20who%20have%20grown%20up%20with%20a%20lowered%20threshold%20for%20what's%20considered%20harmful%2C%20are%20in%20conversation%20with%20their%20parents%2C%20who%20have%20a%20much%20narrower%20and%20more%20severe%20definition%20of%20what%20gets%20labeled%20that%20way%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20often%20there's%20a%20great%20amount%20of%20misunderstanding%20between%20the%20generations%20where%20the%20adult%20child%20might%20say%2C%20'well%2C%20you%20emotionally%20abused%20me%2C%20you%20harmed%20me%2C%20you%20neglected%20me.'%20And%20the%20parent%20is%20like%2C%20'Look%2C%20I%20was%20raised%20with%20abusive%20parents%2C%20you%20did%20not%20have%20an%20abusive%20childhood.'%20And%20as%20you%20could%20imagine%2C%20those%20conversations%20don't%20go%20very%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20Coleman%20believes%20repair%2C%20although%20not%20always%20possible%2C%20is%20the%20better%20option%20for%20everyone.%20If%20you're%20missing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-cut-off-contact-with-my-dad-like-meghan-markle-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut-off%20parent%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20are%20worried%20about%20letting%20them%20back%20into%20your%20life%2C%20he%20shared%20three%20signs%20that%20it's%20safe%20to%20reconnect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYour%20parents%20are%20taking%20responsibility%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EColeman%20helps%20parents%20whose%20adult%20children%20have%20gone%20no-contact%20try%20to%20turn%20things%20around.%20He%20helps%20them%20write%20their%20kid%20a%20letter%2C%20which%20can%20help%20reestablish%20contact%2C%20and%20encourages%20them%20to%20take%20responsibility%20and%20not%20defend%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20parent%20is%20showing%20signs%20of%20self-reflection%20and%20a%20willingness%20to%20renegotiate%20your%20relationship%2C%20it%20might%20be%20time%20to%20start%20rebuilding%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParents%20need%20to%20own%20their%20part%20and%20use%20the%20adult%20child's%20language%20without%20explaining%20it%20away%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20say%2C%20look%2C%20it's%20clear%20I%20had%20blind%20spots%20that%20I%20wasn't%20aware%20of%20that%20felt%20emotionally%20abusive%20to%20you%2C%20but%20I'm%20glad%20you%20let%20me%20know.%20It's%20something%20I%20can%20work%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20indication%20of%20this%20is%20a%20positive%20step%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYou%20know%20what%20you%20can%20and%20can't%20tolerate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEstrangement%20can%20sometimes%20be%20a%20way%20for%20an%20adult%20child%20to%20work%20on%20their%20own%20life%20away%20from%20their%20family%2C%20Coleman%20said%2C%20and%20to%20eventually%20return%20feeling%20stronger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20a%20parent%20who's%20negative%2C%20distant%2C%20or%20rejects%20or%20guilt-trips%20you%2C%20for%20example%2C%20your%20readiness%20to%20reengage%20with%20them%20will%20partly%20be%20linked%20to%20your%20own%20resilience%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20need%20to%20assess%20your%20ability%20to%20not%20internalize%20the%20w