r.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-finance-editorial-standards%23rating-banking-product%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20banking%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20write%20unbiased%20product%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Taryn%20Williams%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F610812a5ea74d40019ba2131%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22384%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Taryn%20Williams.%3Cp%3ETaryn%20Williams%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20January%202021%2C%20my%20net%20worth%20was%20-%2415%2C000.%20By%20July%2C%20it%20was%20%2415%2C000%2C%20thanks%20to%20three%20steps.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20stopped%20paying%20my%20student%20loans%20while%20payments%20were%20paused%20and%20instead%20invested%20that%20money.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20set%20a%20savings%20goal%20every%20month%2C%20then%20did%20everything%20in%20my%20power%20to%20reach%20it%2C%20including%20side%20work.%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-interest-accounts-today%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20my%20adult%20life%20%E2%80%94%20I%20reached%20a%20positive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-net-worth%5C%22%3Enet%20worth%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20a%20first-generation%20college%20graduate%20with%20a%20Master's%20degree%20who%20spent%20most%20of%20my%20working%20life%20underemployed%2C%20this%20felt%20amazing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20let%20me%20note%20my%20privileges%3A%20I%20am%20a%20white%20person%20from%20the%20suburbs%20who%20had%20the%20luck%20of%20attending%20an%20elite%20university%20with%20a%20very%20significant%20financial%20aid%20package.%20Being%20underemployed%20was%20always%20a%20choice%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20not%20the%20case%20for%20most%20Americans%20in%20that%20situation.%20I%20chose%20to%20pursue%20opportunities%20like%20a%20Fulbright%20scholarship%20and%20AmeriCorps%20position%20in%20lieu%20of%20a%20stable%20and%20relatively%20well-paying%20job%20for%20the%20experiences.%20These%20are%20privileges%20not%20everyone%20is%20afforded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20privileges%20aside%2C%20however%2C%20I%20have%20not%20received%20any%20cash%20windfalls%20or%20inheritances.%20Prior%20to%20this%2C%20I%20had%20never%20even%20made%20more%20than%20%2440%2C000%20in%20a%20single%20year%20.%20Despite%20this%2C%20my%20net%20worth%20increased%20from%20-%2415%2C000%20to%20%2415%2C000%20between%20January%20and%20July%202021.%20Here%20are%20some%20of%20the%20ways%20I%20made%20that%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20I%20changed%20my%20mindset%20and%20adjusted%20my%20planning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20so%20long%2C%20the%20student%20debt%20from%20my%20Master's%20degree%20has%20loomed%20over%20me%20and%20made%20it%20challenging%20to%20think%20about%20anything%20else.%20I%20was%20sitting%20on%20over%20%2450%2C000%20of%20debt%20after%20school%20and%20have%20barely%20made%20a%20dent%20in%20it%20over%20the%20years.%20It%20quickly%20became%20my%20sole%20focus%3A%20Every%20extra%20bit%20of%20money%20I%20received%20went%20toward%20that%20debt%20because%20I%20couldn't%20imagine%20feeling%20happy%20and%20free%20until%20it%20was%20gone.%20Several%20years%20later%20%E2%80%94%20and%20still%20%2437%2C000%20in%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20I%20have%20realized%20that%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20continue%20on%20this%20path%3B%20I%20can%20look%20at%20it%20differently.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20realizing%20this%2C%20I%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20pause%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffederal-vs-private-student-loans%5C%22%3Efederal%20loan%20payments%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February%20of%202021.%20I%20had%20already%20knocked%20out%20the%20four%20smallest%20loans%20(they%20ranged%20from%20%241%2C000%20to%20%243%2C000)%20using%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fdebt-snowball-vs-debt-avalanche%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edebt%20snowball%20%3C%2Fa%3Eapproach%20and%20could%20see%20that%20I%20was%20beginning%20to%20make%20progress.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20I%20realized%20paying%20all%20of%20my%20extra%20money%20toward%20loans%20that%20weren't%20accruing%20interest%20during%20the%20pandemic%20wasn't%20the%20best%20way%20to%20build%20wealth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20I%20started%20investing%20more%20(through%20both%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-robo-advisors%5C%22%3Erobo-advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20self-chosen%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%3ERoth%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E%20trades)%20and%20eventually%20started%20to%20see%20some%20growth.%20Since%20I%20made%20the%20choice%20to%20focus%20on%20building%20wealth%20instead%20of%20student%20loan%20repayment%2C%20I%20have%20maxed%20out%20my%20Roth%20IRA%20for%20the%20first%20time%20and%20rebuilt%20my%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%3Eemergency%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20(which%20was%20depleted%20by%20the%20chaos%20that%20was%202020).%20Together%2C%20these%20accounted%20for%20an%20increase%20of%20%2412%2C000%20in%20my%20net%20worth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20I%20set%20obtainable%20monthly%20goals%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20step%20%E2%80%94%20though%20it%20seems%20simple%20%E2%80%94%20probably%20had%20the%20largest%20effect%20on%20my%20overall%20increase.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20regular%20monthly%20transfers%20I%20have%20set%20up%20to%20my%20accounts%2C%20I%20made%20a%20separate%2C%20realistic%20financial%20goal%20each%20month.%20When%20my%20personal%20investment%20account%20was%20at%20around%20%243%2C800%2C%20for%20example%2C%20my%20goal%20for%20the%20next%20month%20was%20%245%2C000%20in%20that%20account.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20set%20one%20goal%20each%20month%20%E2%80%94%20each%20for%20a%20different%20account%20%E2%80%94%20and%20put%20everything%20extra%20toward%20that%20goal%20(like%20my%20stimulus%20checks).%20After%20I%20deposited%20this%20money%20into%20my%20investment%20accounts%2C%20the%20magic%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-compound-interest%5C%22%3Ecompound%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E%20took%20over%2C%20and%20my%20investments%20started%20to%20increase%20exponentially.%20All%20told%2C%20I%20was%20about%20%246%2C000%20richer%20in%20July%20than%20in%20January%20due%20to%20reaching%20these%20goals%20and%20reinvesting%20all%20interest%20and%20dividends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20close%20but%20didn't%20think%20I%20was%20going%20to%20make%20it%2C%20I%20sought%20opportunities%20to%20earn%20extra%20money%20or%20worked%20hard%20to%20cut%20my%20budget%20in%20other%20areas.%20It%20was%20like%20a%20video%20game%20I%20played%20with%20myself%20%E2%80%94%20except%20the%20point%20totals%20were%20real%20money%2C%20and%20the%20prize%20was%20a%20better%20financial%20foundation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20I%20dedicated%20time%20each%20week%20to%20seeking%20additional%20income%20sources%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20side%20hustling%20and%20freelancing%20aren't%20for%20everyone%2C%20but%20there%20is%20usually%20some%20way%20for%20everyone%20to%20make%20a%20little%20extra%20money.%20For%20me%2C%20this%20meant%20dedicating%20a%20specific%20time%20each%20week%20to%20seeking%20out%20additional%20income%20streams.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20someone%20who%20lives%20in%20the%20Alaskan%20Bush%2C%20my%20opportunities%20are%20more%20limited%20than%20most%20%E2%80%94%20there%20are%20no%20Craigslist%20%26quot%3Bgigs%26quot%3B%20or%20service%20jobs%20available%2C%20period.%20Instead%2C%20I%20put%20aside%20a%20specific%20time%20each%20week%20that%20I%20spent%20researching%20any%20possibility%20to%20increase%20my%20income.%20I%20used%20this%20time%20to%20build%20up%20my%20freelance%20portfolio%20and%20find%20opportunities%20my%20full-time%20job%20offered%20that%20I%20wasn't%20already%20taking%20advantage%20of.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20these%20different%20sources%20accounted%20for%20an%20additional%20%245%2C000%2B%20that%20I%20invested%20over%20six%20months%20%E2%80%94%20which%20allowed%20me%20to%20surpass%20my%20original%20net%20worth%20goal%20for%20this%20time%20period.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20financial%20success%20stories%20are%20flashy%2C%20but%20mine%20is%20proof%20that%20they%20don't%20need%20to%20be.%20Making%20consistent%20financial%20choices%20really%20does%20add%20up%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20it%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20it%20at%20the%20time.%20Three%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20made%20the%20first%20deposit%20into%20my%20Roth%20IRA%20and%20today%20that%20account%20makes%20up%20a%20substantial%20portion%20of%20my%20net%20worth.%20I'm%20not%20a%20perfect%20example%20%E2%80%94%20I%20still%20have%20%2437%2C000%20in%20student%20loans%20%E2%80%94%20but%20maybe%20next%20time%20I%20will%20be%20writing%20about%20how%20I%20am%20now%20debt-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20in%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20July%202021.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-increased-my-net-worth-months-2024-03%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710848221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60df2f5a4a93e20019129a79%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-increased-my-net-worth-months-2024-03%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Even%20though%20she%20never%20made%20more%20than%20%2440%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20her%20net%20worth%20increased%20thanks%20to%20dedicated%20saving%2C%20investing%2C%20and%20smart%20debt%20management.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22taryn.mary.williams%40gmail.com%20(Taryn%20Williams)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-increased-my-net-worth-months-2024-03%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Political%20Parties'%20Bizarre%20Replies%20As%20Poll%20Body%20Seeks%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Info%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commission's%20request%20to%20parties%20for%20details%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20received%20by%20them%20elicited%20myriad%2C%20and%20often%20unsolicited%2C%20responses%20--%20one%20party%20seeking%20its%20deregistration%20and%20another%20noting%20that%20its%20chief%20personally%20donates%20Rs%20500%20once%20every%20three%20months%20to%20the%20party%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20responses%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20some%20parties%20gave%20explanations%20for%20not%20receiving%20any%20donation%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20while%20others%20cited%20their%20inability%20to%20provide%20the%20requested%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Maharashtrawadi%20Gomantak%20Party%20cited%20its%20status%20as%20a%20new%20party%20and%20claimed%20it%20had%20not%20garnered%20any%20votes%20in%20elections%20and%20hence%20had%20no%20details%20to%20provide.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20Sarvjan%20Lok%20Shakti%20party%20submitted%20a%20handwritten%20note%20stating%20that%20it%20had%20not%20received%20any%20donation%20as%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bharat%20Ka%20Kisan%20Mazdoor%20Party%20expressed%20frustration%2C%20lamenting%20their%20lack%20of%20recognition%20and%20claiming%20no%20support%20from%20industrialists%20or%20capitalists%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20party%20not%20receiving%20any%20funds%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Tamil%20Nadu-based%20Tamilar%20Desiya%20Munnani%20cited%20health%20issues%20of%20its%20leadership%20for%20its%20inability%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20notice%20within%20the%20given%20time%20frame.%20It%20also%20mentioned%20that%20it%20had%20not%20received%20any%20donation%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20until%20September%2030%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Makkal%20Nala%20Kazhagam%20noted%20that%20its%20president%20personally%20deposits%20money%20into%20the%20party%20account%20every%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BParty%20president%20S%20Sathiyamoorthy%20is%20depositing%20his%20own%20money%20Rs%20500%20once%20in%20three%20months%20in%20party%20account%20in%20the%20concerned%20bank%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kannada%20Naadu%20Party%2C%20which%20has%20since%20passed%20a%20resolution%20for%20dissolution%2C%20submitted%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20requesting%20its%20de-recognition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B...resolutions%20passed%20at%20the%20respective%20meetings%20had%20been%20forwarded%20to%20your%20good%20offices%20and%20we%20are%20awaiting%20your%20confirmation%20of%20de-recognition%20as%20a%20political%20party%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%20in%20the%20response