dth%3A%20318px)%2085vw%2C%20318px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20144212%2FIMG_2915-1-746x1024.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22318%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20144212%2FIMG_2915-1-746x1024.jpg%20746w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20144212%2FIMG_2915-1-219x300.jpg%20219w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20144212%2FIMG_2915-1.jpg%20874w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697965%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22437%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty.%20Photo%3A%20Intifada%20P.%20Basheer%20and%20Azam%20Abbas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThose%20who%20were%20allegedly%20made%20to%20attend%20the%20event%20came%20from%20departments%20such%20as%20school%20education%2C%20higher%20education%2C%20agriculture%2C%20social%20welfare%20and%20the%20Srinagar%20municipal%20corporation.%20Locals%20who%20were%20barred%20from%20attending%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwed-high-hopes-of-meeting-the-pm-say-kashmiris-who-werent-allowed-to-enter-the-stadium%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%20they%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewanted%20to%20talk%20to%20the%20Modi%20about%20their%20problems.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBeing%20left%20out%20was%20almost%20like%20a%20metaphor%20for%20them.%20For%20many%2C%20it%20was%20a%20reminder%20of%20how%20the%20job%20market%20had%20forgotten%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20youth.%20Akhter%2C%20an%20unemployed%20graduate%2C%20who%20requested%20that%20he%20only%20be%20mentioned%20by%20his%20first%20name%2C%20asks%2C%20%E2%80%9CShould%20we%20hope%20for%20jobs%20or%20should%20we%20not%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFrom%20calculations%20to%20cafes%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20hunting%20for%20jobs%2C%20I%20ended%20up%20completing%20degrees%20just%20for%20measly%20recruitment%20drives%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20one%20Iqbal%20Ahmed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20completed%20my%20MSc%20in%20Biotechnology%20in%202016.%20Then%20I%20did%20a%20BEd%20degree%20for%20some%20posts%20that%20were%20announced.%20Thousands%20would%20apply%20for%20five%20to%20six%20teaching%20job%20posts.%20Then%20I%20also%20did%20a%20two-year%20diploma%20course%20in%20Operation%20Theatre%20training.%20Despite%20all%20this%2C%20I%20am%20jobless%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ahmed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAhmed%20says%20he%20took%20various%20loans%20from%20friends%20and%20family%2C%20to%20invest%20in%20a%20Kashmiri%20caf%C3%A9%20brand%2C%20which%20has%20over%2035%20outlets%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20mainland%20India.%20Ahmed%20credits%20Kashmiri%20entrepreneur%20Javid%20Parsa%20for%20mentoring%20him%20when%20he%20needed%20it%20the%20most.%20His%20degrees%2C%20he%20stresses%2C%20proved%20useless.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20I%20am%20not%20a%20job%20seeker%2C%20by%20Allah%E2%80%99s%20grace%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20a%20job%20giver%E2%80%9D%20Ahmed%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EParsa%2C%20founder%20of%20a%20Kashmiri%20restaurant%20chain%2C%20has%20had%20his%20share%20of%20mentoring%20hundreds%20of%20educated%20yet%20unemployed%20youth.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20main%20motivation%20behind%20leaving%20my%20corporate%20job%20in%20Hyderabad%20and%20returning%20to%20Kashmir%20in%202014%20was%20essentially%20so%20I%20could%20help%20my%20people%20amidst%20this%20absolute%20dearth%20of%20job%20opportunities%2C%E2%80%9D%20Parsa%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EParsa%20believes%20that%20there%20is%20a%20massive%20youth%20population%20in%20the%20Union%20Territory%20which%20is%20unemployed%20and%20now%20unmoved%20by%20the%20political%20promises%20made%20to%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20share%20job%20openings%20at%20my%20restaurant%2C%20exceptionally%20educated%20graduates%20and%20post-graduates%20contact%20me%20for%20wait%20staff%20jobs%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20tells%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20the%20private%20sector%20is%20as%20good%20as%20non-existent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDecaying%20degrees%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEach%20morning%20Afshan%20Rashid%20travels%20a%20distance%20of%2060%20kms%20from%20Ganderbal%20to%20reach%20her%20ancestral%20land%20in%20Pulwama%E2%80%99s%20Lassipora.%20%E2%80%9CFarming%20is%20an%20intense%2C%20mindful%20and%20continuous%20activity%2C%20it%20requires%20utmost%20attention%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20usual%20farm%20day%20consists%20of%20many%20activities%20such%20as%20feeding%20chickens%2C%20milking%20cows%2C%20watering%20shrubbery%20and%20trees%2C%20switching%20on%20drip%20irrigation%2C%20de-weeding%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERashid%2C%20a%20media%20professional%20by%20education%20chose%20the%20farming%20life%20out%20of%20affection%20for%20her%20mother.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20started%20this%20initiative%20on%20a%20small%20scale%2C%20and%20started%20receiving%20such%20great%20response%20on%20Instagram%20for%20these%20simple%20farm%20videos%20we%20would%20post.%20Many%20unemployed%20persons%20would%20tell%20us%20how%20their%20unemployment%20%E2%80%93%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20were%20educated%20%E2%80%93%20was%20making%20them%20consider%20farming%20to%20earn%20a%20living%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rashid%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERashid%20too%20tries%20to%20mentor%20as%20many%20unemployed%20young%20men%20and%20women%20as%20possible%2C%20and%20tries%20to%20guide%20them%20towards%20government%20schemes%20and%20subsidies%20that%20help%20budding%20farmers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMusaib%20Nazeer%2C%20an%20MBA%20graduate%2C%20is%20currently%20running%20a%20branch%20of%20Parsa%E2%80%99s%20restaurant%20in%20Srinagar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENazeer%20says%20he%20struggled%20to%20adjust%20to%20the%20reality%20that%20so%20few%20job%20options%20were%20available%20in%20the%20region.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20unemployment%20here%20and%20this%20creates%20a%20whole%20new%20layer%20of%20challenges.%20Over-qualified%20individuals%20are%20forced%20to%20settle%20for%20jobs%20which%20do%20not%20match%20their%20calibre.%20This%20negates%20the%20whole%20idea%20of%20education%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nazeer%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20is%20common%20to%20have%20over-qualified%20people%20apply%20in%20various%20capacities%20at%20the%20restaurant%20he%20manages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERiyaz%20Bhat%2C%20a%20graduate%20in%20political%20science%20knows%20this%20all%20too%20well.%20At%2029%2C%20he%20currently%20works%20as%20a%20waiter.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20should%20think%20about%20us%2C%20give%20us%20ways%20to%20put%20our%20knowledge%20to%20use%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDr.%20Uzma%20Saleem%20Malik%2C%20lecturer%20at%20a%20government%20college%20in%20Jammu%2C%20has%20seen%20the%20impact%20that%20lack%20of%20opportunities%20can%20have%20on%20the%20educated%20unemployed%20very%20closely.%20Due%20to%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20robust%20private%20sector%20or%20corporate%20culture%2C%20several%20educated%20persons%20in%20the%20region%20are%20also%20desperately%20trying%20to%20crack%20government%20job%20exams.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20brutal.%20Sometimes%20when%20I%20review%20ID%20cards%20while%20conducting%20exams%2C%20I%20see%20that%20those%20born%20in%20the%20late%2080s%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20crack%20SSB%20exams%20which%20offer%20meagre%20salaries%2C%E2%80%9D%20Malik%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMalik%20also%20juxtaposes%20the%20situation%20to%20those%20in%20metro%20cities.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20qualified%20PhD%20holder%20in%20Delhi%2C%20or%20any%20other%20metro%20city%2C%20is%20bound%20to%20have%20various%20avenues%20to%20gain%20employment.%20Here%2C%20posts%20are%20few%2C%20work%20expectation%20is%20massive%20and%20salaries%20are%20miniscule.%20There%20are%20only%20a%20handful%20universities%20here%2C%20they%20also%20may%20or%20may%20not%20advertise%20posts%20of%20all%20departments.%20That%20also%20restricts%20employment%20opportunities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERequesting%20anonymity%2C%20a%20PhD%20scholar%20from%20Kashmir%20said%20that%20after%20completing%20her%20PhD%20in%20a%20political%20science%20topic%2C%20she%20had%20qualified%20for%20the%20University%20Grants%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20National%20Eligibility%20Test%20and%20State-Level%20Eligibility%20Test.%20She%20claimed%20that%20for%20an%20assistant%20professor%E2%80%99s%20job%20alone%2C%20s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Echolars%20of%20this%20region%20face%20verification%20attempts%20by%20police%20and%20other%20investigation%20departments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOther%20locals%20whom%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20spoke%20to%20said%20that%20private%20sector%20in%20the%20region%20has%20been%20reduced%20to%20handicrafts%2C%20hospitality%2C%20and%20entrepreneurship.%20Despite%20political%20claims%2C%20they%20argued%2C%20there%20was%20no%20investment%20by%20private%20players%20in%20the%20region%20in%20education%2C%20research%20and%20civil%20society%20organisations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20December%202022%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Edata%20released%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20revealed%20that%20the%20total%20investment%20in%20the%20region%20in%202021-22%20was%20Rs%20376.76%20crore%2C%20down%20from%20Rs%20412.74%20crore%20in%202020-21%20and%20a%20massive%20drop%20of%2055%25%20from%20Rs%20840.55%20crore%20in%202017-18.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDisappointing%20data%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EApart%20from%20rising%20dissatisfaction%20and%20decaying%20degrees%2C%20restricted%20job%20prospects%20are%20pushing%20Kashmiri%20students%20to%20reassess%20their%20educational%20trajectories.%20In%202023%2C%20the%20admission%20rate%20in%20educational%20institutions%20in%20the%20region%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffrontline.thehindu.com%2Fsociety%2Fjammu-and-kashmir-saw-the-highest-attempted-suicide-rate-in-india-in-2022%2Farticle67744235.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eappallingly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20low%20with%20colleges%20witnessing%20a%2040.6%20%25%20decrease%20in%20admissions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJavid%20Ahmed%20Tenga%2C%20president%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EKashmir%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%20and%20Industry%20(KCCI)%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20unemployment%20numbers%2C%20there%20must%20be%20such%20policies%20introduced%20by%20the%20government%20which%20cater%20to%20both%20the%20uneducated%20and%20educated.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20definitely%20need%20drives%20to%20skill%20the%20unemployed%2C%20as%20for%20the%20educated%20unemployed%2C%20private%20sector%20needs%20to%20be%20harnessed%20in%20a%20way%20that%20their%20precious%20time%20is%20not%20wasted%20while%20looking%20for%20jobs.%20As%20PM%20Modi%20has%20allowed%20for%20%E2%80%98ease%20of%20doing%20business%E2%80%99%20in%20other%20states%2C%20J%26amp%3BK%20should%20also%20be%20taken%20into%20that%20fold%2C%20to%20reduce%20our%20unemployment%20numbers%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tenga%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20April%202023%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cb%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3EJ%26amp%3BK%20held%20the%20third%20spot%20on%20the%20list%20of%20highest%20unemployment%20rates%20in%20India%20at%20an%20alarming%2023.1%25%20.%20This%20marked%20a%20jump%20of%206%25%20from%20March%E2%80%99s%20rate%20of%2017.1%20%25%2C%20as%20per%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy%20(CMIE).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20July%202023%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20unemployment%20rate%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EJ%26amp%3BK%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20stood%20at%2018.3%25%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fjammu-and-kashmir-unemployment-rate-is-a-staggering-18-3-the-national-average-is-4242006%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eaccording%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20MHA%20data%20quoted%20during%20a%20reply%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20The%20national%20unemployment%20average%20stood%20at%20around%208%25%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20unemployment%20numbers%20are%20not%20limited%20to%20the%20number%20of%20people%20living%20without%20livelihood.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20latest%20data%20from%20the%20National%20Crime%20Records%20Bureau%20(NCRB)%2C%20J%26amp%3BK%20had%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20attempted%20suicides%20in%202022.%20Out%20of%20the%201%2C769%20suicide%20cases%20recorded%20by%20the%20NCRB%20across%20India%20in%202022%2C%20the%20UT%20saw%20497%20deaths%20by%20suicide.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20December%205%2C%202023%2C%20the%20MHA%20said%20that%20around%2078%20persons%20committed%20suicide%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20between%202020%20to%202022%20due%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.greaterkashmir.com%2Fkashmir%2Funemployment-forced-78-persons-to-commit-suicide-in-jk-in-2-years-mha%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eunemployment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20also%20noteworthy%20that%20the%20NCRB%20report%20states%20that%20since%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20in%202019%2C%20the%20UT%20saw%20at%20least%20450%20cases%20of%20suicide%2C%20this%20number%20further%20worsened%20in%202021%20with%20the%20toll%20sitting%20at%20586%20cases.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20replying%20to%20a%20query%20raised%20by%20MP%20Vijayakumar%20who%20had%20asked%20whether%20the%20issue%20of%20unemployment%20was%20the%20main%20cause%20of%20youth%20dying%20by%20suicide%20in%20the%20country%2C%20the%20Minister%20of%20State%20in%20the%20MHA%2C%20Nityanand%20Rai%2C%20said%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eofficial%20statistics%20revealed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%204%2C88%2C009%20suicides%20%E2%80%93%201%2C53%2C052%20in%202020%2C%201%2C64%2C033%20in%202021%2C%20and%201%2C70%2C924%20in%202022%20were%20reported%20throughout%20the%20country%20from%202020%20to%202022.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E78%20suicides%20including%2046%20in%202020%2C%2015%20in%202021%20and%2017%20in%202022%20were%20reported%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.greaterkashmir.com%2Fkashmir%2Funemployment-forced-78-persons-to-commit-suicide-in-jk-in-2-years-mha%2F%5C%22%3Eowing%20to%20unemployment%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710847819000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F28134446%2F3891925784_eb02c9d8e3_o.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Floans-exams-waiting-tables-jk-youth-say-their-futures-negate-their-education%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Due%20to%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20robust%20private%20sector%20or%20corporate%20culture%2C%20several%20educated%20individuals%20in%20the%20region%20are%20either%20unemployed%20or%20desperately%20trying%20to%20crack%20government%20job%20exams.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Floans-exams-waiting-tables-jk-youth-say-their-futures-negate-their-education%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UK%20Teacher%20Who%20Had%20Sexual%20Relationship%20With%20Student%20Banned%20For%20Life